parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to feel soft or spongy, leading to inconsistent braking performance, which can increase the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
requires double pumping to achieve solid braking
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The misalignment of the front brake caliper can cause the brake pads to wear unevenly, leading to inconsistent braking performance, which can increase the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The front brake rotor hits one brake pad before the other
brake pedal feels soft or spongy.
